{
  "page": "Clegane (father of Gregor and Sandor)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Clegane\" title=\"House Clegane\"><img alt=\"House Clegane.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/50px-House_Clegane.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/75px-House_Clegane.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/100px-House_Clegane.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Clegane</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Clegane\" title=\"House Clegane\"><img alt=\"House Clegane.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/50px-House_Clegane.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/75px-House_Clegane.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b6/House_Clegane.svg/100px-House_Clegane.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ser Clegane by kallielef.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ee/Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png/350px-Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ee/Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png/525px-Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png 1.5x, /images/e/ee/Ser_Clegane_by_kallielef.png 2x\" /></a><div>Ser Clegane, by Kallielef ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Clegane%27s_Keep\" title=\"Clegane&#39;s Keep\">Clegane's Keep</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Clegane\" title=\"House Clegane\">House Clegane</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Clegane_(founder)\" title=\"Clegane (founder)\">Clegane</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nUnknown</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a></li><li>Daughter</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The second <b>Clegane</b> was the father of <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a>. His first name is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clegane_(father_of_Gregor_and_Sandor)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Clegane was born the son of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kennelmaster\" title=\"Kennelmaster\">kennelmaster</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. One <a href=\"/index.php/Autumn\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Autumn\">autumn</a> year, <a href=\"/index.php/Clegane_(founder)\" title=\"Clegane (founder)\">his father</a> saved Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> from a <a href=\"/index.php/Lion\" title=\"Lion\">lioness</a>. Tytos rewarded the kennelmaster with a <a href=\"/index.php/Knighthood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knighthood\">knighthood</a>, lands and a <a href=\"/index.php/Clegane%27s_Keep\" title=\"Clegane&#39;s Keep\">towerhouse</a>, and took his son as his <a href=\"/index.php/Squire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Squire\">squire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Some time later, Clegane inherited the keep and lands from his father.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> When his son <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor</a> was seven years old, and his son <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor</a> was twelve, a woodcarver set up shop in the village by the keep, and gifted toys to the Cleganes to buy favor. Sandor desired his brother's gift, a jointed wooden <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>, and took it to play with, though he was afraid of what the brutal Gregor might do. When Gregor found him, he shoved the side of Sandor's face into the burning coals of a brazier and held him there while he screamed, and only three grown men could drag Gregor off his brother. The Cleganes' <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a> attempted to heal the burns with ointments, and Ser Clegane explained the burns to others by claiming that his son's bedding had caught fire.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>However, there are still rumors that Gregor was involved in Sandor's burning. Ser Clegane's young daughter died mysteriously, and Gregor is rumored to have been involved with that as well. Finally, the knight himself died in a hunting accident, and it is implied he was actually killed by his son Gregor. Sandor left home the day of his father's death to become a <a href=\"/index.php/Sworn_sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sworn sword\">sworn sword</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>, and he has never returned.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Clegane_(father_of_Gregor_and_Sandor)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\